\pard\f0\fs28 Evergreen dwarf shrubs; leaves alternate, subsessile. Flowers 5-merous, on long pedicels in the axils of foliage-leaves. Sepals connate at the base. Corolla rotate, with short tube and deeply lobed limb. Stamens 10; anthers without appendages. Fruit a septicidal capsule; seeds with close-fitting testa.
