\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. K. angustifolia} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 391 (1753). Stems up to 150 cm but often much less, erect or ascending; young twigs terete, glabrous. Leaves 20-60 × 8-18 mm, opposite or in whorls of 3, elliptical to oblong, petiolate, entire, sparsely puberulent, ferruginous beneath when young; margin flat or slightly revolute. Corymbs axillary, on upper part of previous year's growth; pedicels glandular-puberulent. Sepals herbaceous, acute; corolla 7-12 mm in diameter, bright reddish-pink.{\i  Cultivated for ornament and naturalized in Germany and N.W. England.} [Br Ge.] ({\i E. North America.})
