\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. K. polifolia} Wangenh.,{\i  Schr. Ges. Naturf. Freunde Berlin }{\b 8}({\b 2}): 130 (1788). Stems up to 70 cm, ascending or erect, slender; young twigs with 2 angular ridges, pubescent. Leaves 10-30 × 2-8 mm, mostly opposite, linear- to elliptic-oblong, subsessile, entire, glabrous, glaucous or whitish beneath; margin usually strongly revolute. Corymbs terminal; pedicels glabrous. Sepals scarious, obtuse; corolla 10-20 mm in diameter, purplish-pink.{\i  Cultivated for ornament, and naturalized in a bog in S.E. England}. [Br.] ({\i North America.})
